anl48_bdhpd.description: Dividend History Pay Date Column Information.

anl48_bdhrd.description: Dividend History Record Date Column Information.

anl48_bdvd_curr_dvd_health.description: The Dividend Health Score is calculated based on a company's fundamentals and ratings by rating agencies ranging from -100 to 100. The three significant ranges are: -100 to -50 where fundamentals suggest the company cannot sustain the current trend of dividend payments; -50 to 50 where the company can likely maintain the current trend of dividend payments; and 50 to 100 where the company has the ability to increase the amount of their dividend beyond their previous trend.

anl48_bdvd_next_est_ex_dt.description: Next forecasted dividend ex-date. It is calculated based on historical trend in the previous dividend ex-dates.

anl48_bedhga.description: Gross Dividend History Amount Column Information.

anl48_bedhgad.description: Gross Dividend History Announce Date Column Information.

anl48_bedhged.description: Gross Dividend History Ex-Date Column Information.

anl48_bedhgpd.description: Gross Dividend History Pay Date Column Information.

anl48_bedhgrd.description: Gross Dividend History Record Date Column Information.

anl48_bnedd.description: Next forecasted dividend declared date. It is calculated based on trends in the previous dividend declared dates.

anl48_bnepd.description: Next forecasted dividend pay date. It is calculated based on trends in the previous dividend pay dates.

anl48_bp12m_dip.description: Total dividend projection in index points for 1 year in the future. It is the sum of the following calculation for each stock in the index.

anl48_bp12m_yld.description: Projected 12-month dividend yield. This is formulated by summing the next 12 months' dividends divided by the current stock price.

anl48_bp3y_dg.description: Projected dividend per share (DPS) growth rate over the next 3 years, based on the trailing 12-month dividend starting 3 years from today's date. This dividend amount is then divided by the current trailing 12-month dividend amount, annualized.

anl48_bpda.description: Next forecasted dividend per share (DPS) amount; it reveals per unit forecasts when looking at Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs). The forecasts are calculated by analysts based on 7 factors: Company Guidance, Health Score, Industry Analysis, Put-Call Parity, Trend Tool, Regression Analysis, and Analysts.

anl48_bulk_bdvd_all_projections_ibs.description: Serial number that is assigned to a specific security type.

anl48_bulk_bdvd_all_projections_par_amt.description: Count of unique IDs of industry participants. Industry stands for an aggregate view of all  equity clearance activity for the date, symbol, and transaction type in question.

anl48_bulk_count_index_members.description: The number of member stocks of the index. The field will return a number for indices that have member information.

anl48_bulk_dvd_hist_ibs.description: Serial number that is assigned to a specific security type.

anl48_bulk_dvd_hist_par_amt.description: Count of unique IDs of industry participants. Industry stands for an aggregate view of all  equity clearance activity for the date, symbol, and transaction type in question.

anl48_bulk_eqy_dvd_hist_gross_ibs.description: Serial number that is assigned to a specific security type.

anl48_bulk_eqy_dvd_hist_gross_par_amt.description: Count of unique IDs of industry participants. Industry stands for an aggregate view of all  equity clearance activity for the date, symbol, and transaction type in question.

anl48_bulk_idivisor.description: The Divisor is an arbitrary number chosen at the starting point of an index to fix the index starting value (example 1000.00). The divisor is then adjusted when capitalization amendments are made to the constituents of the index allowing the index value to remain comparable at all times.

anl48_bulk_indx_typ.description: Returns the Type of Index. Possible returns are: 1 = Price Weighted, 2 = Capitalization Weighted, 3 = Equally Weighted, 4 = Modified Capitalization Weighted, 5 = Total Return, 6 = Basket Weighted.

anl48_count_index_members.description: The number of member stocks of the index. The field will return a number for indices that have member information.

anl48_dvd_declared_dt.description: The date on which a company announces a dividend distribution.

anl48_dvd_pay_dt.description: The date the company begins distribution of the earlier reported dividend.

anl48_dvd_record_dt.description: The date, on the close of which the company considers holders of the security as being entitled to the dividend payment.

anl48_dvd_xe.description: Count of unique IDs of industry participants. Industry stands for an aggregate view of all  equity clearance activity for the date, symbol, and transaction type in question.

anl48_edg3yr_g.description: Growth rate over 3 years in gross dividend per share. Calculated as: (Current year's dividend per share / Dividend per share 3 years prior), raised to the power of one-third, minus 1, times 100. Dividends per share include Interim and Final payments, as well as all Abnormal Dividends. Dividend amounts are adjusted for stock splits and other corporate actions.

anl48_equity_bulk_bdvd_all_projections_i.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_equity_bulk_dvd_hist_ibc.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_equity_bulk_eqy_dvd_hist_gross_ibc.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_equity_dvd_sh_last.description: Net dividend amount per share of the most recently announced dividend. If there is no dividend announced with a future ex-date, the field returns the net dividend amount per share of the most recently paid dividend. Returns the amount in the currency represented by Dividend Currency (DV010, DVD_CRNCY). Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past 6 months only.

anl48_equity_ibc.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_equity_ldg.description: The most recently announced gross dividend: the net dividend plus any tax credit where applicable. Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past 6 months only. SPX Index, SML Index and MID Index displayed S&P (Standard and Poors) provided EPS (Earning per Share) prior to 6/30/1998.

anl48_equity_m21_dly_dvd_yqe.description: The sum of gross dividend per share amounts that have gone ex-dividend over the prior 12 months, divided by the current stock price. Note: gross and net dividend amounts are assumed to be the same when only one of them is reported.

anl48_equity_td_xe_dvd.description: First date the security trades without entitlement to the current dividend. Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past 6 months only.

anl48_ibs.description: Serial number that is assigned to a specific security type.

anl48_idivisor.description: The Divisor is an arbitrary number chosen at the starting point of an index to fix the index starting value (example 1000.00). The divisor is then adjusted when capitalization amendments are made to the constituents of the index allowing the index value to remain comparable at all times.

anl48_index_bulk_ibc.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_index_dvd_sh_last.description: Net dividend amount per share of the most recently announced dividend. If there is no dividend announced with a future ex-date, the field returns the net dividend amount per share of the most recently paid dividend. Returns the amount in the currency represented by Dividend Currency (DV010, DVD_CRNCY). Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past 6 months only.

anl48_index_ibc.description: Number that is assigned to all companies that issue securities.

anl48_index_ldg.description: The most recently announced gross dividend: the net dividend plus any tax credit where applicable. Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past 6 months only. SPX Index, SML Index, and MID Index displayed S&P (Standard and Poor's) provided EPS (Earning per Share) prior to 6/30/1998.

anl48_index_m21_dly_dvd_yqe.description: The sum of gross dividend per share amounts that have gone ex-dividend over the prior 12 months, divided by the current stock price. Note: gross and net dividend amounts are assumed to be the same when only one of them is reported.

anl48_index_td_xe_dvd.description: First date the security trades without entitlement to the current dividend. Equity Index: Returns a value based on dividends occurring in the past six months only.

anl48_indx_typ.description: Returns the Type of Index. Possible returns are: 1 = Price Weighted, 2 = Capitalization Weighted, 3 = Equally Weighted, 4 = Modified Capitalization Weighted, 5 = Total Return, 6 = Basket Weighted.

anl48_m21_hs_dvd.description: Calculated by adding the gross dividend amounts for all dividend types that have gone 'ex' over the past 12 months based on the dividend frequency. This total includes taxes, any related dividend fees or tax-related credits. The current value returned will be in the security's Dividend Currency (DV010, DVD_CRNCY) and the historical value will be in the pricing Currency (DS004, CRNCY).

anl48_par_amt.description: Count of unique IDs of industry participants. Industry stands for an aggregate view of all  equity clearance activity for the date, symbol, and transaction type in question.

anl48_td_xe_dvd_cb.description: Dividend Forecasts Ex Date Column Information.
